        <a href="about.html">About</a>
    </nav>
    <main>
        <h2>Steps After Changing Filament</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Prepare the New Filament:</strong> Ensure the filament is fully loaded and free of tangles. Use a filament cutter to trim excess material.</li>
            <li><strong>Load into the Printer:</strong> Insert the new filament into the hopper and close the printer's door. Allow the printer to detect the filament.</li>
            <li><strong>Adjust Settings:</strong> Update the extruder temperature, flow rate, and print speed in the printer's firmware according to the material type.</li>
            <li><strong>Test Print:</strong> Run a test print to ensure the new filament is working correctly. Check for under-extrusion or clogging issues.</li>
            <li><strong>Post-Change Checks:</strong> Clean the nozzle, check bed adhesion, and verify that all mechanical components are functioning properly.</li>
        </ol>
    </main>
