        <a href="about.html">About</a>
    </nav>
    <main>
        <h2>Common Issues and How to Fix Them</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Under-extrusion:</strong> Check the extruder temperature, flow rate, and belt tension. Clean the nozzle if there's clogging.</li>
            <li><strong>Layer Adhesion Problems:</strong> Ensure the bed is level and use a raft or brim for better adhesion. Try adjusting the first layer height.</li>
            <li><strong>Nozzle Clogs:</strong> Use a needle to clear blockages. Clean the nozzle with a cleaning rod and ensure the filament is not contaminated.</li>
            <li><strong>Print Warping:</strong> Increase the bed temperature, use a raft, or apply an adhesive sheet for better adhesion.</li>
            <li><strong>Printer Jumps:</strong> Check the X/Y axis belts for tension and ensure the printer is on a stable surface.</li>
        </ul>
    </main>
